                            <comment id="13015762" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Tue, 5 Apr 2011 05:20:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;HBaseAdmin.getCatalogTracker() calls HConnectionManager.getConnection() which uses Configuration as key in HBASE_INSTANCES.&lt;br/&gt;
Since we want to reuse connection to the same cluster, maybe we can do this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
      connection = HBASE_INSTANCES.get(conf.get(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;hbase.zookeeper.quorum&quot;&lt;/span&gt;));
      &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (connection == &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;) {
        connection = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; HConnectionImplementation(conf);
        HBASE_INSTANCES.put(conf.get(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;hbase.zookeeper.quorum&quot;&lt;/span&gt;), connection);
      }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Of course, the above would break deleteConnection() which requires reference counting.&lt;br/&gt;
So maybe we can use a wrapper for (refcount, connection) tuple and store the wrapper object as value in HBASE_INSTANCES ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13016199" author="jdcryans" created="Wed, 6 Apr 2011 00:30:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The main concern is that different components in the same JVM have different connections, so a closed client connection doesn&apos;t also close a region server connection (like in most tests). The HBaseAdmin constructor should just copy the configuration upfront.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13016609" author="jdcryans" created="Wed, 6 Apr 2011 23:34:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch that adds the copy in HBA&apos;s constructor and removes the copy in getCatalogTracker, passes unit tests.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13016687" author="stack" created="Thu, 7 Apr 2011 04:48:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is this the right way to go?  The javadoc on #getCatalogTracker says:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;@return A new CatalogTracker instance; call {@link #cleanupCatalogTracker(CatalogTracker)} to cleanup the returned catalog tracker.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is the problem that cleanupCatalogTracker is not being called?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13017194" author="jdcryans" created="Thu, 7 Apr 2011 22:59:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch that fixes the places where it wasn&apos;t cleaning the CT, also I still do the configuration copy in the constructor to be safer.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13017198" author="stack" created="Thu, 7 Apr 2011 23:08:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 Lets go w/ this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13017200" author="jdcryans" created="Thu, 7 Apr 2011 23:25:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to branch and trunk, thanks for the reviews Stack!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13018776" author="hudson" created="Tue, 12 Apr 2011 09:28:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in HBase-TRUNK #1846 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/HBase-TRUNK/1846/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/HBase-TRUNK/1846/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="15016868" author="lars_francke" created="Fri, 20 Nov 2015 12:41:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue was closed as part of a bulk closing operation on 2015-11-20. All issues that have been resolved and where all fixVersions have been released have been closed (following discussions on the mailing list).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
